<subSubSection pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="529">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Note:</emphasis>
Wijnands (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Bot. Commelins</emphasis>
: 81. 1981) argued that the typification by Roessler should be rejected because the thesis in which the Linnaean name was published was based largely on specimens lent to Linnaeus by Burman. While this is generally true, 1027.4 (LINN) is annotated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1760" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Gorteria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squarrosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Gorteria squarrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Linnaeus, and appears to be original material for the name. Consequently, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Roessler’s" pageNumber="529">Roessler's</normalizedToken>
typification is accepted here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
